    <note>Zhao(1) Buxi [19414] Zhejiang TZ, 125.19b identifies him as a Wuzhou jinshi, but he was buried in Yuhang county, address of his sons. However, an uncle, Shifen [20443] (grandson of Zonghui(2) [19411], Buxi's great grandfather), was the father-in-law of Liu(2) Bangguang [20447], a Wuzhou, Wuyi resident, which suggests a temporary stay in Wuzhou during the transition period of this branch of the lineage's move to the South. There is an alternate version of his mingzi used in some sources. SHY:ZG, 72.11b; Ye Shi, WJ, 26.512-518. CBD, 4, 3404.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1174:  Dismissed (fangba) as Chengdu yunpan.</note>
